<item>
            <title>[OAK-824] Query engine: automatic expansion of &quot;x=1 or x=2&quot; to &quot;(x is not null) and (x=1 or x=2)&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-824</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Queries with conditions of the type &quot;x=1 or x=2&quot; currently don&apos;t use an index. An index (on property existance) could be used if the condition is automatically expanded to &quot;(x is not null) and (x=1 or x=2)&quot;. This should be relatively easy to implement in the query engine (I hope).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
